: Was known as the &quot;Daytona 3 Hour Continental&quot;, up to 1964.
: Was known as the &quot;Daytona 2000&quot;, up until 1965 before becoming a 24 hour race following that year.
: The race was shortened to 6 hours, partly over concerns that the 3 liter formula one engined prototypes were not reliable enough for the entire 24 hours.

